We are witnessing the official residence of the once most powerful man north of the Alps, the preactor of the CCAA.
What CCAA means, a visitor wants to know.
"The abbreviation stands for "Colonia Claudia Ara Agrippinensium", which means in good German as much as "City of Roman Law and the City of the Agrippinser, founded under Emperor Claudius at the Place of the Altar for the Imperial cult".
And the praetorium is the former governor's palace, the centre of power of the Roman Empire on the Rhine.
From the entrance hall of the exhibition, a tunnel access to the Roman sewer, which has been preserved here over a length of around 120 metres, leads.
"You can walk along the so-called Cloaca Maxima if you want," Schulze makes the guests feel at home.
Schulze still has a surprise.
After he has brought the key at the cash register, he leads the group to a 16-meter-deep, walk-in shaft.
